According to the Filesystem Hierarchy Standard (FHS), what is the correct location for add-on application software packages?
A)  /etc
B)  /var
C)  /tmp
D)  /opt
D
D. The /opt hierarchy is used for add- on application software packages. The /etc hier-archy is configuration information, while /var is also data files but variable files such asmail files. The /tmp directory is for temporary files. Because each path begins with a /, it isconsidered an absolute path.
